<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19756</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort Sam Houston</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3456. Following received General Pershing dated October 24: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Villa in control of all towns from Bustillos west to Madera and
                                    all territory as far north as Namiquipa and Santa Clara and
                                    probably east to railroad. Carrancista detachment of 100 men at
                                    Cruces to-night. Deserters say Villa still threatens to make
                                    attack on Americans as soon as he gets more men and
                                    equipment.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Funston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>